  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple layers of national and international regulations:\n\n1. International Standards\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Key Legislative Frameworks\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Patriot Act\n- Money Laundering Control Act\n\n3. Regulatory Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping obligations\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential business license revocation\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial crime investigative units\n- Specialized law enforcement teams\n- Interagency cooperation\n- International information sharing\n\n6. Compliance Obligations\n- Financial institutions\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Real estate sectors\n- Professional service providers\n\n7. Preventative Measures\n- Risk assessment\n- Transaction screening\n- Enhanced due diligence\n- Internal control systems\n\nThe framework aims to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes.",
